summary:
The Security Council, 
Having considered the report on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force, 
1. Calls upon parties to implement resolution 338 (1973) immediately; 
2. Welcomes efforts to implement the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, 
requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary action and keep the Council informed, 
and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish such acts; 
3. Renews the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for six months, until 30 June 2008; 
4. Requests the Secretary-General to report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973) by the end of this period.
